## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-197">Una búsqueda asincrónica puede mostrar los resultados se detectan al buscar resultados adicionales al mismo tiempo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-197">An asynchronous search can show results as they are found while simultaneously searching for additional results.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-198">Esto es útil para tareas como rellenar cuadros de lista.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-198">This is useful for tasks such as populating list boxes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-199">El valor predeterminado de esta propiedad es `false`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-199">The default setting for this property is `false`.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-200">En el ejemplo de C# siguiente se muestra cómo crear una búsqueda asincrónica.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-200">The following C# example shows how to create an asynchronous search.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
//Set the Asynchronous property to true.  
src.Asynchronous = true;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-204">El atributo que se establece esta propiedad en debe ser un atributo de nombre distintivo, por ejemplo, miembro o modifican.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-204">The attribute that this property is set to must be a distinguished name attribute, such as member or managedBy.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-205">El atributo puede ser uno o varios valores.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-205">The attribute can be either single or multi-valued.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-206">Para obtener más información, vea los temas de Active Directory Schema "[miembro](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/adschema/adschema/a_member.asp)"y"[Managed By](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/adschema/adschema/a_managedby.asp)" en MSDN Library en [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-206">For more information, see the adschema topics "[Member](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/adschema/adschema/a_member.asp)" and "[Managed-By](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/adschema/adschema/a_managedby.asp)" in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-207">La búsqueda se realiza en los objetos que se identifican por el nombre distintivo que se especifica en el atributo del objeto base.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-207">The search is performed against the objects that are identified by the distinguished name that is specified in the attribute of the base object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-208">Por ejemplo, si el objeto base es una clase de grupo de Active Directory Schema y <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> se establece en "member", la búsqueda se realizará en todos los objetos que son miembros del grupo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-208">For example, if the base object is an adschema group class and the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> is set to "member," then the search will be performed against all objects that are members of the group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-209">Para obtener más información, vea el tema relativo a la clase en la biblioteca de MSDN en "Grupo" [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-209">For more information, see the adschema "Group" class topic in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-210">Cuando el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propiedad se utiliza, el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> propiedad debe establecerse en <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-210">When the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property is used, the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property must be set to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.SearchScope.Base>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-211">Si el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> propiedad se establece en cualquier otro valor, establecer el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propiedad producirá una <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-211">If the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchScope%2A> property is set to any other value, setting the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property will throw an <xref:System.ArgumentException>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-212">Para obtener más información, vea el tema "Realizar una consulta de ámbito de atributo" en MSDN Library en [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library)).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-212">For more information, see the "Performing an Attribute Scope Query" topic in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library)).</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-213">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo utilizar el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> propiedad con el atributo de miembro para obtener los miembros de un grupo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-213">The following example shows how to use the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.AttributeScopeQuery%2A> property with the member attribute to get the members of a group.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-214">A continuación, imprime los nombres y apellidos de los miembros y sus números de teléfono.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-214">It then prints out the first and last names of the members and their telephone numbers.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
DirectoryEntry group = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=MyGroup, …");  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher(group "(&(objectClass=user)(objectCategory=Person))");  
src.AttributeScopedQuery = "member";  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("sn");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("givenName");  
src.PropertiesToLoad.Add("telephoneNumber");  
foreach(SearchResult res in src.FindAll())  
{  
    Console.WriteLine("…");  
}  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-232">En el ejemplo de C# siguiente se muestra cómo establecer el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> propiedad <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , de modo que Desreferencia los alias al buscar subordinados y localizar objetos base.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-232">The following C# example shows how to set the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.DerefAlias%2A> property to <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DereferenceAlias.Always> , so that it dereferences aliases when both searching subordinates and locating base objects.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
// Bind to the users container.  
DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("LDAP://CN=users,DC=fabrikam,DC=com");  
// Create a DirectorySearcher object.  
DirectorySearcher mySearcher = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
// Set DerefAlias to Always.  
src.DerefAlias = DerefenceAlias.Always;  
//Use the FindAll method to get search results.  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-242">En el ejemplo siguiente se muestra cómo devolver una colección de nombres distintivos en formato hexadecimal.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-242">The following example shows how to return a collection of distinguished names in hexadecimal format.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.ExtendedDN = ExtendedDN.HexString;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-303">Si <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> es una referencia nula (`Nothing` en Visual Basic), la raíz de la búsqueda se establece en la raíz del dominio que el servidor está utilizando actualmente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-303">If <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.SearchRoot%2A> is a null reference (`Nothing` in Visual Basic), the search root is set to the root of the domain that your server is currently using.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-304">Hay varias maneras de buscar en el catálogo global:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-304">There are several ways to search in the global catalog:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="dd343-305">Enumerar el catálogo global y seleccione al primer elemento secundario.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-305">Enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="dd343-306">Especifique el nombre del servidor.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-306">Specify the server name.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-307">Utilice la función DsGetDcName para encontrar el catálogo global.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-307">Use the DsGetDcName function to find the global catalog.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="dd343-308">Para obtener más información sobre la función DsGetDcName, vea el tema "DsGetDcName" en MSDN Library en [ http://msdn.microsoft.com/library ](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-308">For more information on the DsGetDcName function, see the topic "DsGetDcName" in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="dd343-309">Obtener el objeto RootDSE del catálogo global y solicitar "rootNamingContext".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-309">Get the RootDSE  of the global catalog and ask for "rootNamingContext".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="dd343-310">Usar el catálogo global, especificar una ruta de acceso de búsqueda como si utilizara LDAP.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-310">Use the global catalog, specifying a search path as if using LDAP.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="dd343-311">Por ejemplo, "GC: / / OU =..., DC =..., DC =...".</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-311">For example, "GC://OU=..., DC=..., DC=...".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="dd343-312">El siguiente código de C# muestra cómo enumerar el catálogo global y seleccionar al primer elemento secundario.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-312">The following C# code shows how to enumerate the global catalog and pick the first child.</span></span>  
  
    ```csharp  
    DirectoryEntry entry = new DirectoryEntry("GC://forestname");  
    IEnumerator ie = entry.Children.GetEnumerator();  
    ie.MoveNext();  
    entry = (DirectoryEntry)ie.Current;  
    DirectorySearcher search = new DirectorySearcher(entry);  
    ```

  
  
## Examples  
  
```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.SecurityMasks = SecurityMasks.Dacl | SecurityMasks.Owner;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  
  
```

  
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="dd343-350">En el ejemplo de C# siguiente se muestra cómo establecer el <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.Tombstone%2A> propiedad `true`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="dd343-350">The following C# example shows how to set the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectorySearcher.Tombstone%2A> property to `true`.</span></span>  
  
